Package com.vaadin.polymer.platinum.event

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DeviceChangedEvent
    Fired when Bluetooth device picked by user gets updated.
    DeviceChangedEvent.Detail  
    PlatinumBluetoothAutoWriteErrorEvent
    Fired when an error occurs while writing automatically to a characteristic.
    PlatinumBluetoothAutoWriteErrorEvent.Detail  
    PlatinumPushMessagingClickEvent
    Fired when a notification is clicked that had the current page as the
    click URL.
    PlatinumPushMessagingClickEvent.Detail  
    PlatinumPushMessagingErrorEvent
    Fired when an error occurs while enabling or disabling notifications
    PlatinumPushMessagingErrorEvent.Detail  
    PlatinumPushMessagingPushEvent
    Fired when a push message is received but no notification is shown.
    This happens when the click URL is for this page and the page is
    visible to the user on the screen.
    PlatinumPushMessagingPushEvent.Detail  
    ServiceWorkerErrorEvent
    Fired when an error prevents the service worker installation from completing.
    ServiceWorkerErrorEvent.Detail  
    ServiceWorkerInstalledEvent
    Fired when the initial service worker installation completes successfully.
    The service worker will normally only be installed once, the first time a page with a
    <platinum-sw-register> element is visited in a given browser.
    ServiceWorkerInstalledEvent.Detail  
    ServiceWorkerUpdatedEvent
    Fired when the service worker update flow completes successfully.
    If you make changes to your <platinum-sw-register> configuration (i.e.
    ServiceWorkerUpdatedEvent.Detail  
    ValueChangedEvent
    Fired when value gets changed during a notification session.
    ValueChangedEvent.Detail
